cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on robotic in-hand manipulation and proposes a hierarchical method for controlling finger motion.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses learned policies on the mid-level of the hierarchy.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses deep reinforcement learning and evaluates the approach in simulation.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the robustness of the approach to observation noise.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but relevant as the paper proposes a control method for manipulating objects.
